    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Siste gradum quaeso sine te levet umbra tenacem <lb n="2"/>hospes iter durum est quid teris usque viae <lb n="3"/>audi pauca moram facient mea dicta labores <note>sic</note> <lb n="4"/>sed memor haec imo pectore conde tuo <lb n="5"/>crudeles divi Sthygias <note>sic</note> quicumque paludis <note>sic</note> <lb n="6"/>incolitis nulli qua datur ire retro <lb n="7"/>quid vos inmatura iuvat quae vestra futurast <lb n="8"/>post modo consumpto tempore turba tuo <lb n="9"/>fletibus adsiduis luget maestissima mater <lb n="10"/><supplied reason="lost">quae p</supplied>rior <supplied reason="lost">occidere quam Naiamira dari eigni!</supplied> <lb n="11"/><supplied reason="lost">debuit ut superi pia fata t</supplied>ulissent <lb n="12"/><supplied reason="lost">et pater hoc titulo debui</supplied>t ante legi <lb n="13"/><supplied reason="lost">his ergo mea dicta refer de</supplied>sistat humatam <lb n="14"/><supplied reason="lost">ulterius lachrumis! sollic</supplied>itasse suis <lb n="15"/><supplied reason="lost">sum defleta satis finem dece</supplied>t esse dolori <lb n="16"/><supplied reason="lost">quid semel</supplied> occubui nul<supplied reason="lost">la quer</supplied>ella iuvat
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Von der verschollen geglaubten Inschrift CIL IX 3071 wurden zwei Fragmente gefunden. Maße des anderen Fragments: 17 x 18. Die vor der Tochter verstorbenen Eltern sind nicht namentlich in der Inschrift genannt. (B): Z. 2: CIL: via[m]; CLE: viam; Z. 3: CIL: faciunt; labor[i]s; CLE: faciunt; laboris; Z. 5: CIL, CLE: Stygias quicunque paludes; Z. 7: CIL, CLE: futura est; Z. 9: CIL: m[a]estissima; CLE: mestissima; Z. 11 Anfang: CLE: igni; Z. 16: CIL, CLE: occubuit.</p>
            </div>
